            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "It would be pretty simple to turn off any unit conversion on output.  This means you would get the same as I get when setting **PROJ_LENGTH_UNIT** to inch.  I think those results are more sensible in most but not all cases.  Or, we could let **-Q** get a small enhancement:\r\n\r\n**-Q**[**c**|**i**|**p**|**n**]\r\n\r\nQuick mode for scalar calculation. Shorthand for **-Ca -N**1/0 **-T**0/0/1. In this mode, constants may have dimension units (i.e., **c**, **i**, **p**) and will be converted to internal inches before computing.  If one or more constants with units are encountered then the final answer will be reported in the unit set by **PROJ_LENGTH_UNIT**, unless overridden by appending on of **c**|**i**|**p**. Alternatively, append **n** for a non-dimensional result, meaning there is no unit conversion during output.\r\n\r\nI think this would be a pretty good solution and documentation, @Esteban82 ?",
